Prompt content:

# CC PROMPT — v2.44.1 — feat(tests): DB-backed test run history — test_runs + test_run_results + test_suites + schedules

## What this does

The current test system stores results as a flat JSON file (`data/test_results.json`).
No history, no comparison, no scheduling. This prompt adds the DB layer:

- `test_suites` — named groupings of test IDs with a config (memory on/off, categories, etc.)
- `test_runs` — one row per run: suite_id, config snapshot, start/end, score
- `test_run_results` — one row per test case per run: pass/fail, tools, steps, duration
- `test_schedules` — cron-like schedule for automatic runs

API endpoints added:
- `GET  /api/tests/runs`                 — list all runs (paginated)
- `GET  /api/tests/runs/{run_id}`        — full run with results
- `GET  /api/tests/runs/compare?ids=a,b,c,d` — up to 4 runs side by side
- `POST /api/tests/run`                  — existing, extended to write to DB
- `GET  /api/tests/suites`              — list suites
- `POST /api/tests/suites`              — create/update suite
- `DELETE /api/tests/suites/{id}`       — delete suite
- `GET  /api/tests/schedules`           — list schedules
- `POST /api/tests/schedules`           — create schedule
- `DELETE /api/tests/schedules/{id}`    — delete schedule
- `GET  /api/tests/trend`               — score over time per suite

Version bump: 2.44.0 → 2.44.1.

